        "For example: \"Dear [Manager's/Senior Leader's Name], please accept my best wishes for a prosperous New Year. I deeply appreciate your steadfast leadership and the clear vision you've articulated for [Company Name]. I am enthusiastic about the opportunities ahead in 2026 and committed to supporting our collective goals. Wishing you and your family a healthy and successful year.\" These messages demonstrate professional maturity and respect for the hierarchical structure, reinforcing your role as a dedicated and engaged member of the organization.",
        "### Wishes for Subordinates and Direct Reports",
        "As a leader, sending New Year messages to my subordinates and direct reports is not merely a courtesy; it's a vital opportunity to reinforce team spirit, recognize individual efforts, and set a positive, encouraging tone for the year ahead. I find it incredibly important to communicate genuine appreciation for their hard work and dedication, while also fostering an environment of continuous growth and support.",
        "When crafting these messages, I always ensure they are:",
